{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "| Variable Name | Variable Label | Type | Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format* | Role | CDISC Notes | Core |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGSPID | Sponsor-Defined Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor-defined reference number. May be printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: Line number on the ECG page. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGBEATNO | ECG Beat Number | Num | | Identifier | A sequence number that identifies the beat within an ECG. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGTESTCD | ECG Test or Examination Short Name | Char | (EGTESTCD)(HETSTESTCD) | Topic | Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in EGTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in EGTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., \"1TEST\" is not valid). EGTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: \"HR\", \"QRS\", \"PR\". Test codes are in 2 separate codelists, 1 for tests based on regular 10-second ECGs (EGTESTCD) and 1 for tests based on Holter monitoring (HETSTESTCD). | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(EGTESTCD)(HETSTESTCD)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGTEST | ECG Test or Examination Name | Char | (EGTEST)(HETTEST) | Synonym Qualifier | Used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in EGTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: \"PR Interval\", \"Aggregate\", \"QRS Duration\", \"Aggregate\". Test names are in 2 separate codelists, 1 for tests based on regular 10-second ECGs (EGTEST) and 1 for tests based on Holter monitoring (HETTEST). | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(EGTEST)(HETTEST)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGCAT | Category for ECG | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | Used to categorize ECG observations across subjects. Examples: \"MEASUREMENT\", \"FINDING\", \"INTERVAL\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGSCAT | Subcategory for ECG | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | A further categorization of the EG. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGPOS | ECG Position of Subject | Char | (POSITION) | Record Qualifier | Position of the subject during a measurement or examination. Examples: \"SUPINE\", \"STANDING\", \"SITTING\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(POSITION)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGORRES | Result or Finding in Original Units | Char | | Result Qualifier | Result of the ECG measurement or finding as originally received or collected. Examples of expected values are \"62\" or \"0.151\" when the result is an interval or measurement, or \"ATRIAL FIBRILLATION\" when the result is a finding. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGORRESU | Original Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for EGORRES. Examples: \"beats/min\", \"msec\", \"mV\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(UNIT)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGSTRESC | Character Result/Finding in Std Format | Char | (EGSTRESC)(HESTRESC)(NORMABMN) | Result Qualifier | Contains the result value for all findings copied or derived from EGORRES, in a standard format or standard units. EGSTRESC should store all results or findings in a character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in EGSTRESN. For example, if a test has results of 62 beats/min, then EGORRES = \"62\", EGORRESU = \"beats/min\", EGSTRESC = \"62\", EGSTRESN = 62, and EGSTRESU = \"beats/min\". For other examples, see Original and Standardized Result Values and Findings for Results. EGSTRESC is used to store results for abnormal test result findings based on regular 10-second ECGs, HESTRESC for abnormal test results based on Holter monitoring, and NORMABMN for generic test result responses to ECG \"Interpretation\". Examples: \"NORMAL\", \"ABNORMAL\", \"FLUTTER\", \"ATRIAL FIBRILLATION\". | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(EGSTRESC)(HESTRESC)(NORMABMN)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGSTRESN | Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units | Num | | Result Qualifier | Used for continuous or numeric results of findings in standard format; copied in from EGSTRESC. EGSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGSTRESU | Standardized Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Standardized units used for EGSTRESN and EGSTRESC. EGSTRESU = the unit value used for numeric results. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(UNIT)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate if an ECG was not done, or an ECG measurement was not taken. Should be null if a result exists in EGORRES. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(ND)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0186_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 186, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGREASND | Reason ECG Not Done | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes why a measurement or test was not performed. Examples: \"BROKEN EQUIPMENT\", \"SUBJECT REFUSED\". Used in conjunction with EGSTAT when value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGXFN | ECG External File Path | Char | | Record Qualifier | File name and path for the external ECG waveform file. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGNAM | Vendor Name | Char | | Record Qualifier | Name or identifier of the laboratory or vendor providing the test results. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGMETHOD | Method of Test or Examination | Char | (EGMETHOD) | Record Qualifier | Method of the ECG test. Example: \"12-LEAD STANDARD\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(EGMETHOD)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGLEAD | Lead Location Used for Measurement | Char | (EGLEAD) | Record Qualifier | The lead used for the measurement. Examples: \"LEAD 1\", \"LEAD 2\", \"LEAD aVF\", \"LEAD V1\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(EGLEAD)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGLOBXFL | Last Observation Before Exposure Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Operationally derived indicator used to identify the last non-missing value prior to RFXSTDTC. The value should be \"Y\" or null. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(NY)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGBLFL | Baseline Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Indicator used to identify a baseline value. Should be \"Y\" or null. Note that EGBLFL is retained for backward compatibility. The alternative baseline for derived analysis is in an ADaM dataset. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(NY)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGDRVFL | Derived Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be \"Y\" or null. Records that represent the average of other records, or that do not come from the CRF, or are not as originally collected or received are examples of records that would be derived for the submission datasets. If EGDRVFL=\"Y\", the meaning of the record should be null (see Section 4.1.8.1, Origin Metadata for Variables ). | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(NY)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGEVAL | Evaluator | Char | (EVAL) | Record Qualifier | Role of the person who provided the evaluation. Used only for results that are subjective (e.g., assigned by a person or a group). Should be null for records that contain collected or derived data. Examples: \"INVESTIGATOR\", \"ADJUDICATION COMMITTEE\", \"VENDOR\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(EVAL)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGERVALID | Evaluator Identifier | Char | (MEDEVAL) | Variable Qualifier | Used to distinguish multiple evaluators with the same role recorded in EGEVAL. Examples: \"RADIOLOGIST 1\", \"RADIOLOGIST 2\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(MEDEVAL)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGCLSIG | Clinically Significant Observation | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate whether a collected observation is clinically significant based on judgment. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(NY)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGREPNUM | Repetition Number | Num | | Record Qualifier | The incidence number of a test that is repeated within a given timeframe for the same test. The level of granularity can vary (e.g., yearly, within a visit). Examples: multiple measurements of blood pressure, multiple analyses of a sample. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISITNUM | Visit Number | Num | | Timing | Clinical encounter number. Numeric version of VISIT. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISIT | Visit Name | Char | | Timing | Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISITDY | Planned Study Day of Visit | Num | | Timing | Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
