{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EPOCH | Epoch | Char | (EPOCH) | Timing | Epoch associated with the date/time at which the assessment was made. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CODELIST", "ref": "(EPOCH)"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGDTC | Date/Time of ECG | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date/time of ECG. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGDY | Study Day of ECG | Num | | Timing | Study day of the ECG, measured as integer days. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGTPT | Planned Time Point | Char | | Timing | Name of the planned time point as referenced by EGTPTREF. Not a clock time or a date time variable. Represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See EGTPTNUM and EGTPTREF. Examples: \"Start\", \"5 min post\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGTPTNUM | Planned Time Point Number | Num | | Timing | Numerical version of EGTPT to aid in sorting. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGELTM | Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Planned elapsed time (in ISO 8601) relative to a fixed time point reference (EGTPTREF). Not a clock time or a date time variable. Represented as an ISO 8601 duration. Examples: \"-PT15M\" to represent the period of 8 hours prior or \"PT8H\" to represent 8 hours after the reference point indicated by EGTPTREF. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGTPTREF | Time Point Reference | Char | | Timing | Name of the planned time point indicated by the reference point indicated by EGTPTREF. Name of the planned time point designated by EGTPTREF. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGFRTDTC | Date/Time of Fixed Reference Time Point | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date/time for a fixed reference point as defined by EGTPTREF. Examples: \"PREVIOUS DOSE\", \"PREVIOUS MEAL\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "EG – Assumptions", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "EGREFID is intended to store an identifier (e.g., UUID) for the associated ECG tracing. EGXFN is intended to store the name of and path to the electrocardiogram (ECG) waveform file when it is submitted.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "There are separate codelists for tests and results based on regular 10-second ECGs and for tests and results based on Holter monitoring.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Associations between some ECG abnormality tests and response codelists are described in the ECG codetable (available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/codelists).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "URL", "ref": "https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/codelists"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For non-individual ECG beat data and for aggregate ECG parameter results (e.g., \"QT interval\", \"RR\", \"PR\", \"QRS\"), EGREFID is populated for all unique ECGs, so that submitted SDTM data can be matched to the actual ECGs stored in the ECG warehouse. Therefore, this variable is expected for these types of records.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For individual-beat parameter results, waveform data will not be stored in the warehouse, so there will be no associated identifier for these beats.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The method for QT interval correction is specified in the test name by controlled terminology. EGTESTCD = \"QTCFAG\" and EGTEST = \"QTcF Interval, Aggregate\" is used for Fridericia's formula; EGTESTCD = \"QTCBAG\" and EGTEST = \"QTcB Interval, Aggregate\", is used for Bazett's formula.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "EGBEATNO is used to differentiate between beats in beat-to-beat records.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "EGREPNUM is used to differentiate between multiple repetitions of a test within a given time frame.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "EGNRIND can be added to indicate whether a result falls with respect to reference range defined by EGORNRLO and EGORNRHI. Examples: \"HIGH\", \"LOW\". Clinical significance would be represented as described in Section 4.5.5, Clinical Significance for Findings Observation Class Data, in EGCLSIG (see also EG Example 1).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CROSS_REF", "ref": "Section 4.5.5, Clinical Significance for Findings Observation Class Data"}, {"type": "CROSS_REF", "ref": "EG Example 1"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "When \"QTcF Interval, Aggregate\" or \"QTcF Interval, Aggregate\" is received from a central provider or vendor, the value would go into EGORRES and EGDRVFL would be null (see Section 4.1.8.1, Origin Metadata for Variables ).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [{"type": "CROSS_REF", "ref": "Section 4.1.8.1, Origin Metadata for Variables"}], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0188_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 188, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If this domain is used in conjunction with the ECG QT Correction Model Data (QT domain:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For each QT correction method used in the study, values of EGTESTCD and EGTEST are assigned at the study level.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The sponsor should assign values for EGTESTCD/EGTEST appropriately with clear documentation on what each test code represents. For example, if the protocol calls for computing the top best fit model QTC1AG1 and the second best fit model QTC1AG2, the sponsor could choose to name the top best fit model QTCIAG1 and the second best fit model as QTCIAG2, in rank order.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "By identifiers, timing variables, or findings derived general observation-class qualifiers may be added to the EG domain, but the following qualifiers would not generally be used: --MODIFY, --BODSYS, --SPEC, --SPCCND, --FAST, --SEV. It is recommended that --LOINC not be used.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "EG - Examples", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example shows ECG measurements and other findings from one ECG for one subject.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "EGCAT has been used to group tests.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 1: Shows a measurement of ventricular rate. This result was assessed as not clinically significant (EGCLSIG = \"N\").", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 2: Shows a measurement of PR interval. This result was assessed as clinically significant (EGCLSIG = \"Y\").", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 2-4: These interval measurements were collected in seconds. However, in this submission, the standard unit for these tests was milliseconds, so the results have been converted in EGSTRESC and EGSTRESN.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 5-6: Show \"QTcB Interval, Aggregate\" and \"QTcF Interval, Aggregate\". These results were derived by the sponsor, as indicated by the \"Y\" in the EGDRVFL column. Note that EGORRES is null for these derived records.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 7-10: Show results from tests looking for certain kinds of abnormalities, which have been grouped using EGCAT = \"FINDINGS\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 11: Shows a technical problem represented as the result of the test \"Technical Quality\". Results of this test can be important to the overall understanding of an ECG, but are not truly findings or interpretations about the subject's heart function.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0189_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 189, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 12: Shows the result of the TEST \"Interpretation\" (i.e., the interpretation of the ECG strip as a whole), which for this ECG was \"ABNORMAL\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
